This statement by the President commemorates the 50th anniversary of the signing of the U.S.-Japan Treaty of Mutual Cooperation and Security. The President emphasizes the enduring partnership between the two countries, which has brought prosperity and peace to both nations. The alliance has also benefited the Asia Pacific region and contributed to the progress of the past five decades. The President reaffirms America's commitment to Japan's security and highlights the importance of cooperation in addressing common challenges. The statement calls for renewing the alliance for the 21st century and strengthening the bonds of friendship and common purpose between the two nations.